Class VenueMapFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.app.Fragment
      • com.google.android.gms.maps.MapFragment
        • com.leantegra.wibeat.sdk.rtls.map.VenueMapFragment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentCallbacks, ComponentCallbacks2, View.OnCreateContextMenuListener

    public class VenueMapFragment
extends com.google.android.gms.maps.MapFragment
    A Indoor Map component in an app. This fragment is the simplest way to place a map in an application. It's a wrapper around a view of a map to automatically handle the necessary life cycle needs. Being a fragment, this component can be added to an activity's layout file simply with the XML below.

    A GoogleMap must be acquired using getVenueMapAsync(OnVenueMapReadyCallback). This class automatically initializes the maps system and the view.

    Since:
    1.6.0

    • Method Detail

      • getVenueMapAsync

        public void getVenueMapAsync(@NonNull
                             OnVenueMapReadyCallback onVenueMapReadyCallback)
        Sets a callback object which will be triggered when the VenueMap instance is ready to be used.

        Note that:

        • This method must be called from the main thread.
        • The callback will be executed in the main thread.
        • In the case where Google Play services is not installed on the user's device, the callback will not be triggered until the user installs it.
        • In the rare case where the VenueMap is destroyed immediately after creation, the callback is not triggered.
        • The VenueMap object provided by the callback is non-null.
        Parameters:
        onVenueMapReadyCallback - The callback object that will be triggered when the map is ready to be used.
